[Nouns] liquefaction; liquescence, liquescency; melting (heat) [more]; colliquation, colliquefaction; thaw; liquation, deliquation, deliquescence; lixiviation, dissolution.
solution, apozem, lixivium, infusion, flux.
solvent, menstruum, alkahest.
[Verbs] render liquid [more]; liquefy, run; deliquesce; melt (heat) [more]; solve; dissolve, resolve; liquate; hold in solution; condense, precipitate, rain.
[Adjectives] liquefied, liquescent, liquefiable; deliquescent, soluble, colliquative.
